==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Tubicolae
<hw>Tu*bic"o*lae</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>tubus</ets> a tube + <ets>colere</ets> to inhabit.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A division of annelids including those which
construct, and habitually live in, tubes. The head or anterior segments
usually bear gills and cirri. Called also <altname>Sedentaria</altname>,
and <altname>Capitibranchiata</altname>. See <er>Serpula</er>, and
<er>Sabella</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tubicolar</ent>⟦br⟧
